<!-- Free trial callout -->
<section class="px-6 py-12 bg-base-200">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">30-day SME trial — no credit card</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base-content/80">
      Sign up on the portal, create an org, click "Request trial." You get a signed Ed25519
      license token with the full SME feature set — Postgres, Redis, pgvector, OIDC, 15 gateways,
      10 users. After 30 days the token expires; there's a 7-day grace window where premium
      features keep working with a banner, then premium features lock but <strong>your gateways
      keep protecting traffic forever</strong> — we never turn off detection.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6 flex gap-3 flex-wrap">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/portal">Start the trial</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/trust">Read the security posture first</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Competitive context -->
<section class="px-6 py-12">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Honest about the alternatives</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base-content/80">
      We're not the cheapest option on the market — CrowdSec OSS is free too, if you don't need
      managed blocklists. We're not the most expensive either — DataDome and Cloudflare Bot
      Management both start above $3,000/mo and don't self-host. StyloBot fits the gap:
      self-hosted at every tier, priced for the mid-market that most SaaS bot-defense vendors
      price out of.
    </p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6">
      <table class="table text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Vendor</th><th>Entry</th><th>Mid-market</th><th>Self-host?</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="font-semibold">
            <td>StyloBot</td><td>$0 (OSS)</td><td>$149 – $499/mo</td><td class="text-success">Always</td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td>CrowdSec</td><td>$0 OSS</td><td>$900+/mo blocklists</td><td class="text-success">Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td>CHEQ</td><td>$149/mo</td><td>$249+/mo</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>DataDome</td><td>$3,830/mo</td><td>$4K – $13K/mo</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cloudflare Bot Mgmt</td><td>$3,000/mo floor</td><td>$10K+/mo</td><td class="text-error">No (edge-locked)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Akamai Bot Manager</td><td>Custom (~$8K for SMB)</td><td>$8K – $25K/mo</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td>HUMAN (PerimeterX)</td><td>Quote only</td><td>Enterprise-only</td><td class="text-error">No</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="text-xs text-base-content/50 mt-2">
        Pricing as of April 2026. Sources: vendor marketplaces, G2, public reviews.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="px-6 py-12 bg-base-200">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">FAQ</h2>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Is OSS really fully functional?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          Yes. All 31 detectors, session vectors, local dashboard, SQLite persistence,
          Ollama-backed LLM escalation. The only things not in OSS are central control plane,
          multi-gateway fleet dashboard, Postgres/Redis persistence, and OIDC SSO.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">What happens when my license expires?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          7-day grace window where everything keeps working with a banner. Then premium
          features return <code>402 Payment Required</code> but core detection keeps running
          forever — gateways never stop protecting traffic because of a license lapse.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Can I self-host the customer portal too?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          For licensing / trials / billing, no — stylobot.net is the authority because trial
          tokens need vendor signing. For Enterprise customers with air-gap requirements we
          support offline license activation against a pre-provisioned keypair — contact sales.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Do you take card payments?</h3>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-1 text-sm">
          Stripe integration for Startup/SME monthly + annual lands in a future portal
          iteration. For now, trials are self-serve; paid plans are invoiced. Contact us to
          set up billing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
